# Calculator UI — Merged Input + Results

Reference: `src/pages/calculators/hvac/hvac-heat-pump-calculator/index.astro`

When building or refactoring a single-tool calculator, use **one card** for inputs and live results. Do not use separate input/results cards, sticky gradient sidebars, or `lg:grid-cols-5 gap-6` split layouts.

## Structure

```html
<section id="calculator" class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 pb-12">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 sm:p-8 shadow-sm">
  <h2><!-- one heading for the whole tool, not "Enter details" only --></h2>
  <div class="mt-6 lg:grid lg:grid-cols-2 lg:gap-8 lg:items-start">
    <div class="space-y-6"><!-- inputs + reset --></div>
    <div class="mt-6 lg:mt-0 rounded-xl border border-{accent}-100 bg-{accent}-50 p-5 sm:p-6">
      <!-- live results -->
    </div>
  </div>
  </div>
</section>
```

## Results panel (no gradient)

- Use a **light inset panel**: `bg-{accent}-50 border border-{accent}-100`
- Do **not** use `bg-gradient-to-br`, full-bleed sidebars, `lg:sticky`, or a second outer card
- Hero value: `text-{accent}-600` + large weight (`text-5xl font-extrabold`)
- Stat tiles: `rounded-xl border border-{accent}-100 bg-white p-4`
- Labels: `text-slate-500` / `text-slate-600`; values: `text-slate-900`
- Guidance + breakdown: white inset cards with same accent border
- Disclaimer: `text-slate-500 text-xs`

Replace `{accent}` with the page accent (e.g. `indigo`, `blue`, `cyan`) — match existing input focus rings and icons.

## Responsive

- **Desktop (lg+):** two columns inside one card
- **Mobile:** results stack below inputs (`mt-6 lg:mt-0`) inside the same card

## Refactoring rules

- Keep all result element `id`s unchanged so existing scripts keep working
- Live-update on input change; no Calculate button unless the tool truly needs it
- Reference tables, FAQ, and content below `#calculator` stay separate

## Avoid

```html
<!-- ❌ separate cards with gap -->
<div class="grid lg:grid-cols-5 gap-6">
  <div class="lg:col-span-3 rounded-2xl border ...">inputs</div>
  <div class="lg:col-span-2"><div class="lg:sticky bg-gradient-to-br ...">results</div></div>
</div>

<!-- ❌ full-bleed gradient sidebar inside one card -->
<div class="lg:flex"><div class="lg:flex-1">inputs</div><div class="bg-gradient-to-br lg:w-80">results</div></div>
```
